===Etymology===
1921, from {{der|en|it|fascista}}, from {{m|it|fascio||bundle, bunch}}, in use metonymically for "group of men organized for political purposes" since 1895.  Ultimately with reference to the [[fasces]] or bundles of axes and rods carried before the magistrates of ancient Rome in token of their power of life and death.

